# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: PrisonArc | Scene: OutsideAndAlone2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah was sitting outside near the docks on a bench, watching the ships come and go."
    new "Sarah was sitting outside near the docks on a bench, watching the ships come and go."

    old "It wasn't much for a plan, but watching the motions of the harbor made her feel calm. Allowed her to think."
    new "It wasn't much for a plan, but watching the motions of the harbor made her feel calm. Allowed her to think."

    old "Most of her money was gone, stolen and wasted by Kate."
    new "Most of her money was gone, stolen and wasted by Kate."

    old "She had no allies left in this city, thrown out by the mercenary company."
    new "She had no allies left in this city, thrown out by the mercenary company."

    old "And she couldn't think of a soul left in the world who cared enough for her to intercede on her behalf."
    new "And she couldn't think of a soul left in the world who cared enough for her to intercede on her behalf."

    old "Sarah went down the list of every person she knew, but every name she could recall lived in Rosanna, and she was not sure if they still lived."
    new "Sarah went down the list of every person she knew, but every name she could recall lived in Rosanna, and she was not sure if they still lived."

    old "She concluded that even if she could send a letter, it might be weeks before anyone could send help, and she barely had enough money to survive a day."
    new "She concluded that even if she could send a letter, it might be weeks before anyone could send help, and she barely had enough money to survive a day."

    old "A neighbouring kingdom might take her in, but so dire was the news from across the ocean, that she didn't even know if any still stood against Hassar's horde."
    new "A neighbouring kingdom might take her in, but so dire was the news from across the ocean, that she didn't even know if any still stood against Hassar's horde."

    old "And so, with every attempt at a solution, Sarah returned to the simple reality."
    new "And so, with every attempt at a solution, Sarah returned to the simple reality."

    old "She was alone, in a city, and nobody would come to save her."
    new "She was alone, in a city, and nobody would come to save her."

    old "By the time she had ran through the last idea, night had firmly settled in."
    new "By the time she had ran through the last idea, night had firmly settled in."

    old "With no place to sleep, she walked the city until she came across an alleyway."
    new "With no place to sleep, she walked the city until she came across an alleyway."

    old "The streets around them seemed quiet enough."
    new "The streets around them seemed quiet enough."

    old "She was afraid. She knew Kate had been right, the city was a dangerous place, but exhaustion had also made it impossible to think of much else."
    new "She was afraid. She knew Kate had been right, the city was a dangerous place, but exhaustion had also made it impossible to think of much else."

    old "Crawling behind one of the crates, Sarah imagined she would be out of sight enough to be left alone."
    new "Crawling behind one of the crates, Sarah imagined she would be out of sight enough to be left alone."

    old "Resting her head against one of the sacks, she slowly felt herself begin to fade away."
    new "Resting her head against one of the sacks, she slowly felt herself begin to fade away."

    old "Sarah snapped awake again."
    new "Sarah snapped awake again."

    old "It was still night. How long had she been out for?"
    new "It was still night. How long had she been out for?"

    old "And why did she wake so suddenly."
    new "And why did she wake so suddenly."

    old "Her eyes tried to get used to the dark. There was a shade moving through the alley."
    new "Her eyes tried to get used to the dark. There was a shade moving through the alley."

    old "The voice sounded rough. Sarah felt her heart beat in her chest, the man's voice alerted her."
    new "The voice sounded rough. Sarah felt her heart beat in her chest, the man's voice alerted her."

    old "Brigand\" \"I asked you something girly, you lost?"
    new "Brigand\" \"I asked you something girly, you lost?"

    old "Sarah could now make out the man, leaning against the wall close to her."
    new "Sarah could now make out the man, leaning against the wall close to her."

    old "No, good sir, I'm only resting for a moment."
    new "No, good sir, I'm only resting for a moment."

    old "Brigand\" \"Aah, I see. That's fine, you can rest here if you want."
    new "Brigand\" \"Aah, I see. That's fine, you can rest here if you want."

    old "There was a pause."
    new "There was a pause."

    old "Brigand\" \"But you see, there is just a small problem."
    new "Brigand\" \"But you see, there is just a small problem."

    old "Brigand\" \"This here is my alley, I own it, and I can't just let anybody and everybody sleep here."
    new "Brigand\" \"This here is my alley, I own it, and I can't just let anybody and everybody sleep here."

    old "Brigand\" \"If I let you sleep here for free, soon everybody will want to sleep here, and before long the city guards will come knocking."
    new "Brigand\" \"If I let you sleep here for free, soon everybody will want to sleep here, and before long the city guards will come knocking."

    old "Brigand\" \"Can't have that, can't have that at all."
    new "Brigand\" \"Can't have that, can't have that at all."

    old "Brigand\" \"So I'm afraid, I'll need you to spare some coin."
    new "Brigand\" \"So I'm afraid, I'll need you to spare some coin."

    old "The man held out his hand, clawing for some money to pass hands."
    new "The man held out his hand, clawing for some money to pass hands."

    old "By now, Sarah's eyes had grown accustomed to the dark, and she could better make out the man's frame."
    new "By now, Sarah's eyes had grown accustomed to the dark, and she could better make out the man's frame."

    old "He was tall, and only seemed a bit older than herself. Yet his appearance hinted at having lived a life far rougher than hers."
    new "He was tall, and only seemed a bit older than herself. Yet his appearance hinted at having lived a life far rougher than hers."

    old "I don't have any money, so I'll just leave."
    new "I don't have any money, so I'll just leave."

    old "Suddenly, the man pushed himself away from the wall and came up closer to Sarah, blocking her into the corner behind the crate."
    new "Suddenly, the man pushed himself away from the wall and came up closer to Sarah, blocking her into the corner behind the crate."

    old "Brigand\" \"Sure, you can leave..."
    new "Brigand\" \"Sure, you can leave..."

    old "Brigand\" \"But you already used my alley, so you already owe me some coin for tonight."
    new "Brigand\" \"But you already used my alley, so you already owe me some coin for tonight."

    old "Sarah felt her heart beat faster still."
    new "Sarah felt her heart beat faster still."

    old "I told you, I don't have any money."
    new "I told you, I don't have any money."

    old "Brigand\" \"Well, maybe I've been unclear. You need to pay me. That can be in coin...or some other way..."
    new "Brigand\" \"Well, maybe I've been unclear. You need to pay me. That can be in coin...or some other way..."

    old "The man's eyes drifted across her body as he said the words."
    new "The man's eyes drifted across her body as he said the words."

    old "Sarah knew she was in danger."
    new "Sarah knew she was in danger."

    old "Scream!"
    new "Scream!"

    old "Sarah draws in her breath, filling her lungs with air."
    new "Sarah draws in her breath, filling her lungs with air."

    old "And lets out a deafening scream."
    new "And lets out a deafening scream."

    old "She screams louder and more sharply than she's ever done in her life."
    new "She screams louder and more sharply than she's ever done in her life."

    old "The sound cuts violently through the otherwise silent night."
    new "The sound cuts violently through the otherwise silent night."

    old "Run away."
    new "Run away."

